## Insurance and Direct Billing

We offer direct billing for many major insurance providers. Most extended health benefits plans cover physiotherapy and chiropractic services. To avoid unexpected costs, please confirm with your provider whether a referral is required and what your policy covers before your visit.

## Do I Need a Referral?

In Ontario, you do not need a referral from a doctor to receive physiotherapy, chiropractic, or massage therapy. However, some extended health insurance providers may require a referral for reimbursement. Please check with your insurance provider to confirm if a doctor�s note is needed to process your claim.

## Booking and Cancellation Policy

Appointments may be cancelled or rescheduled up to 24 hours in advance with no penalty. Cancellations with less than 24 hours� notice or missed appointments may be subject to a full appointment charge. Please notify the clinic by phone or email if you need to change your appointment.

## Physiotherapy

Our physiotherapy treatments address pain, injuries, and movement issues through manual therapy, exercise, and education. Sessions may include stretching, mobilizations, and strengthening routines.

## Chiropractic

Chiropractic care focuses on joint health, spinal alignment, and nervous system function. It can support recovery from back pain, tension, and mobility issues.

## Registered Massage Therapy (RMT)

RMT involves therapeutic massage techniques to reduce muscle tension, improve circulation, and relieve pain or stress-related conditions.

## New Patient Intake Process

New clients should arrive 10�15 minutes early to complete their digital intake form. Please bring valid ID and insurance information. Initial assessments typically last 45�60 minutes and include a physical evaluation, a review of your health history, and a discussion of treatment goals.
